<h1>Tagging Reference</h1>

<p>When tagging works or sections with loci, use the <strong>slug</strong> shown to the right of each topic.
Loci should be assigned only when a work or section includes an extended discussion of that topic.
Select the locus that best describes the topic of that section.
Do not select loci where the topic is only briefly mentioned.</p>

<p>Loci may be added to the tree when necessary.
Changes to loci names require updating all work files that reference them.</p>

<pre class="tagging-tree">
{%- macro renderTree(nodes, prefix) -%}
{%- for node in nodes -%}
{%- if loop.last -%}
{%- set connector = prefix + "└── " -%}
{%- set childPrefix = prefix + "    " -%}
{%- else -%}
{%- set connector = prefix + "├── " -%}
{%- set childPrefix = prefix + "│   " -%}
{%- endif -%}
{{ "\n" + connector }}<strong>{{ node.name }}</strong>  <code>{{ node.slug }}</code>
{%- if node.desc -%}
{{ "\n" + childPrefix }}<span class="tree-desc">{{ node.desc }}</span>
{%- endif -%}
{%- if node.children -%}
{{ renderTree(node.children, childPrefix) }}
{%- endif -%}
{%- endfor -%}
{%- endmacro -%}

{%- for node in site.lociTree %}

<strong class="tree-root">{{ node.name }}</strong>  <code>{{ node.slug }}</code>
{%- if node.desc -%}
{{ "\n  " }}<span class="tree-desc">{{ node.desc }}</span>
{%- endif -%}
{%- if node.children -%}
{{ renderTree(node.children, "") }}
{%- endif -%}
{%- endfor %}
</pre>
